title: Tourists record great white shark devouring seal near Alcatraz
text:
Photo: KEVIN SULLIVAN, AP A shark fin in the water is often associated with panic and danger, but there are a lot of myths surrounding sharks that makes them seem scary.

Savage nature was on display when a great white shark devoured a seal just a few feet off Alcatraz Island in full view of gawking tourists, the first attack by the ferocious finned predator in the modern history of San Francisco Bay.
